      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "95be592787d72bdd",
      "text": "In 1997 Flores coauthored a second book, [[Disclosing New Worlds]], with his former mentor [[Hubert Dreyfus]] and fellow Berkeley Ph.D. and BDA executive [[Charles Spinosa]]. In this book, Flores returned to central themes in his writings, such as the configuration of reality and the relationship of knowledge and praxis. The book centers on the idea […]\n"
