        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "f46e6c449f1c18c9",
        "text": "At its peak BDA had 150 employees on three continents and annual billings of $50 million. According to the magazine Fast Company, BDA charged $1 million for Flores's services. By 2007 Flores's net worth was an estimated $40 million. As his wealth grew, so did his reputation. To some he was brusque, intimidating, direct to the point of rudeness, and off-putting. Yet his message and his success in both the academic and business communities transformed him into a cult figure for others.\n\n\n"
